		<div>Once you max your defensive AA's there is a much better chance to live.<br />
<br />
Until then, and with low AC, ya you take a few hits.  Keep yourself runed and some mobs dont chain summon, but rather only summon once per set time so you can get summoned and get some distance.  Sure you will get summoned again, but at least the NPC wsn't beating on you the whole time.<br />
<br />
As for all the other issues.  The wizard class seems to have a bunch of little things that most would agree need tweaking, they just seem to be piling up more as time marches on and things change faster then the class can keep up.<br />
<br />
EQ is designed as a grouping game, that has run off the tracks somewhat.  SOE hates soloing from what I understand, and would illiminate it from the game if they could.  How dare you kill 4 mobs by yourself, that should require a group <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Stick Out Tongue" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
To some extent I agree, grouping should be more beneficial then soloing, but keep it around for those who like it.<br />
<br />
If you raid alot SCS3 rules. Others have already suggested the other AA's.  Get HoD if you don't already.<br />
<br />
Grouping is hit or miss, the best way thrive in EQ today is to have a group or clique you run with to do stuff each day.  The game is slowly beginning to fragment, and the groups who are still intact will do best.<br />
<br />
Don't taunt him with PoF table's, he said he was on VT keyed <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /></div>
