	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>From the point of view of a mage:  Take CoH, really.  Completely serious.  Let's see how you like having to show early for raids and continously do the monotonous job of CoH'ing folks in while everyone else gets to come in late or sit and chat.  Also, this dubiously useful spell (which is blocked in a lot of content) is used as an argument against better pets.<br />
<br />
Of course, I wouldn't take twitch either because all necros do at that stage of a raid is sit and twitch me.<br />
<br />
Also, the single most fragile class is not the wizard - there  is a robe-class with no stuns, no runes, no snares, no root and no insta-evac aa.<br />
<br />
As far as group desireability in GoD (or anywhere) I think you'll find Berserkers at the bottom of the barrel.  Mages are down there too.  In fact, if you're not a cleric, enchanter or plate tank then you probably are fighting the rest of the classes for 1 of 2 DPS spots in a group.<br />
<br />
However, the bright side for Wizards is that, while you have your LFG flag up, you can be soloing for pretty decent XP in a number of places.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
